#Repo readme

Here it is, Gregory — a clean, spacious, Bohm‑aligned top‑level README for the entire UNBN Toolkit repository.
It’s written to feel welcoming, conceptually deep without being intimidating, and structurally clear for GitHub readers who may be encountering the framework for the first time.

You can drop this directly into README.md at the root of the repo.

---

UNBN Toolkit

A modular, generative architecture for modeling worlds, coherence, and transformation.

The UNBN Toolkit is a minimal, extensible framework for exploring how coherent structures arise, evolve, and interact across physics, economics, cognition, and other domains.
It is not a simulation engine in the traditional sense.
It is a generative substrate — a way of expressing systems in terms of:

• State
• Flow
• Constraint
• Interaction
• Symmetry
• Geometry
• Measurement
• Reconfiguration


These eight nodes form the universal kernel of the architecture.
Everything else in the toolkit — classical mechanics, quantum layers, gauge systems, economic cycles, interfaces, time storms — emerges from these same structural primitives.

The goal is simplicity, clarity, and coherence.
The toolkit is designed to be inviting, not overwhelming.

---

Why UNBN?

Most scientific toolkits begin with a domain: physics, economics, cognition.
UNBN begins with structure — the generative patterns that underlie all domains.

This allows:

• cross‑domain modeling
• world‑to‑world translation
• unified coherence analysis
• minimal, readable implementations
• conceptual clarity without heavy abstraction


The toolkit is intentionally small.
It grows only as needed.

