---

Getting Started

Install the toolkit:

pip install -e .


Run an example:

python examples/classical_world_example.py


Or run all examples:

python examples/run_all_examples.py


Each example is small, readable, and designed to show one idea clearly.

---

Philosophy

The UNBN Toolkit is built around a simple idea:

Structure and experience are two faces of the same unfolding process.

The code expresses structure.
The examples express experience.
The documentation expresses the space between them.

The toolkit is not a final theory.
It is a platform for exploration — a way of thinking and building that stays open, modular, and generative.

---

Contributing

Contributions are welcome, especially those that:

• simplify
• clarify
• unify
• reveal new coherence patterns


The architecture grows through refinement, not expansion.

